query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `events` (
  `id` int AUTO_INCREMENT NOT NULL,
  `title` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `slug` varchar(255),
  `chapter` varchar(64),
  `description` text,
  `rules` text,
  `capacity` int NOT NULL,
  `markState` enum('outside','initiate','member','inner_circle','dormant','restricted','revoked') DEFAULT 'initiate',
  `eventVisibility` enum('public','members','inner_circle') DEFAULT 'public',
  `city` varchar(128) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'South Jakarta',
  `locationText` text,
  `locationRevealHoursBefore` int DEFAULT 24,
  `locationRevealAt` timestamp,
  `eventDate` timestamp,
  `startDatetime` timestamp,
  `endDatetime` timestamp,
  `eventStatus` enum('draft','published','completed','cancelled') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'draft',
  `publishedAt` timestamp,
  `createdAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updatedAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  CONSTRAINT `events_id` PRIMARY KEY(`id`)
);
